name: Special Focus: Core Level 5
description:
#### **Special Focus: Core Level 5**

This six week training plan is specifically designed to improve your core strength and pelvic stability, which is key for endurance athletes. With three short focused sessions per week this is the perfect way to get in the extra time to concentrate on the three dimensional segment from shoulder to hip. You can add this as an off-season block or an extra bump to your regular season training. These workouts will target core muscles but will also include considerable demand for the smaller muscles of the upper body.

​

We recommend that you only select Level 5 if you have recently completed Special Focus Core Level 4. As with any of the SYSTM strength plans, take your time with each session and follow the proper progression.

​

This plan may be applied in conjunction with other Special Focused strength plans or with one of the 12 week add-ons for extra core training. However, if you add concurrent strength plans please be mindful that you are getting adequate recovery between workouts.

​

The Special Focus stand alone plans follow a 2:1 progression and have three sessions per week on Monday, Wednesday and Friday.

​

It's time to get after it!
planDescription: This is a 6 week stand alone plan that is designed to target your Upper Body. The plan has 3 workouts per week (M-W-F) and follows a 2 on: 1 off progression.

prospects.name: Core Focus 04
prospects.description:
_Looking to improve ALL of the muscles that make up your core? You’ve come to the right place. The Core Focus series builds up everything from your hip to your shoulders - front, back, and side._

​

We’re getting more complicated now, and this session includes rotational movements which demand power and control against an external load. The combination and order of movements will challenge your core strength and endurance while improving your ability to maintain stability and control when tired.

prospects.name: Core & Hip Mobility C
prospects.description:
This module is a standing-based session designed to improve mobility through your hips, and challenge balance while activating and integrating muscles that are key to core stability. Take your time to work through the movements and focus on quality. Be sure to rotate through the other routines in this series on a regular basis for maximum benefit.

​

Exercises:

- Split Stance Back Bend
- Single-Leg Hip Hinge
- Split Stance Side Bend w/Arms Overhead
- Single-Leg Hip Hinge w/Rotation
- Downward Dog
- Pigeon Stretch

prospects.name: Neck Mobility C
prospects.description:
This session is designed to improve mobility and stability through the cervical spine. It incorporates cervical movement with ground-based body positions to simulate sporting positions like cycling and swimming.

​

Take your time to work through the movements and focus on performing them with control. Do not move into pain. If you have tingling or numbness from any of these movements stop and consult a medical professional. Be sure to rotate through the other routines in this series on a regular basis for maximum benefit.

​

Exercises:

- Cat/Cow Stretch
- Quadruped T-Spine Rotation
- Quadruped Cervical Retraction
- Quadruped Cervical Extension
- Low Plank w/Cervical Retraction
- Low Plank w/Cervical Extension
- Child’s Pose

prospects.name: Core Focus 01
prospects.description:
_Looking to improve ALL of the muscles that make up your core? You’ve come to the right place. The Core Focus series builds up everything from your hip to your shoulders - front, back, and side._

​

To do this, we’ll take you through a variety of contraction types: eccentric (lengthening), concentric (shortening), and isometric (holding a position). The result? Improved core strength, stability, and endurance. You'll find exercises that carry over into other areas of your body, but all of the moves have a significant impact on your core. Level 1 is ideal for very beginners. Even then, you may find some of these moves challenging if you have never attempted them. That’s ok, take your time and pause the video if you need. Soon you’ll be on your way to mastering your core potential. In addition to a mat, you'll need some open wall space for this routine.

​

Unsure if this is the correct strength level for you? [Click here for help.](https://wahoosystm.com/HelpCenterChooseStrengthLevel)

​

**Exercises Included:**

- Split Stance Side Bend w/ Arms Overhead
- Downward Dog
- Quadruped T-Spine Rotation
- Back Extension w/ opp arm & leg raise
- Hamstring Hip Bridge
- Oblique Leg Lifts
- Quadruped w/ alternating arm raise
- Quad w/ leg raises
- Low Side Plank w/ toe-tap front/back
- High Side Plank w/ Hold
- Quad Toes w/ Alternate Arm Raise
- Quadruped Pull In & Hold
- Quadruped Push Out & Hold
- Bird Dogs
- Back Extension with Hold
- Child's Pose

prospects.name: Core & Hip Mobility D
prospects.description:
This standing-based session integrates adduction (towards your body midline) and abduction (away from your body midline) moves to improve stability through your hips and challenge balance while activating and integrating muscles that are key to core stability. Take your time to work through the movements and focus on quality. Be sure to rotate through the other routines in this series on a regular basis for maximum benefit.

​

Exercises:

- Split Stance Back Bend
- Standing Hip Abduction
- Single-Leg Hip Hinge
- Single-Leg Hip Bridge w/Rotation
- Pigeon Stretch
